msgid "Pātimokkhe uddissamāneti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1334</a><term>During the […] recitation of the "
"monastic code</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.9"
msgid "uddisante."
msgstr "<gloss>during the reciting.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.10"
msgid "Evaṃ vadeyyāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1335</a><term>Might say</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.11"
msgid "anācāraṃ ācaritvā—"
msgstr "<gloss>after misbehaving, he thinks,"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.12"
msgid "“aññāṇakena āpannoti jānantū”ti pātimokkhe uddissamāne evaṃ vadeti—"
msgstr ""
"<gloss>“Let them think that I committed these offenses because I didn’t know "
"about the rules.” If, while the monastic code is being recited, he then says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.13"
msgid ""
"“idāneva kho ahaṃ jānāmi, ayampi kira dhammo suttāgato suttapariyāpanno "
"anvaddhamāsaṃ uddesaṃ āgacchatī”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.45\">BD.3.45</a> “Just now did I find out "
"that this rule too has come down in the monastic code, is included in the "
"monastic code, and comes up for recitation every half-month,” then he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.14"
msgid ""
"Tañce mohetukāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ aññe bhikkhū jāneyyuṃ nisinnapubbaṃ iminā "
"bhikkhunā dvattikkhattuṃ pātimokkhe uddissamāne, ko pana vādo bhiyyo, na ca "
"tassa bhikkhuno aññāṇakena mutti atthi, yañca tattha āpattiṃ āpanno, tañca "
"yathādhammo kāretabbo, uttari cassa moho āropetabbo."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1336</a>If other monks know that the monk who wants to "
"deceive has previously sat through at least two or three recitations of the "
"monastic code, then that monk is not let off because of ignorance, and he is "
"to be dealt with according to the rule. Further, he should be charged with "
"deception."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.15"
msgid "“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, āropetabbo."
msgstr "“And, monks, he is to be charged in this way."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.16"
msgid "Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṃgho ñāpetabbo—"
msgstr "A competent and capable monk should inform the Order:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.17"
msgid "‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr ""
"<span class=\"kamma\"><p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1337</a>‘Venerables, let the "
"Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.18"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu pātimokkhe uddissamāne na sādhukaṃ aṭṭhiṃ katvā "
"manasi karoti."
msgstr ""
"This monk so-and-so didn’t pay proper attention when the monastic code was "
"being recited."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.19"
msgid ""
"Yadi saṃghassa pattakallaṃ, saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno mohaṃ āropeyya."
msgstr ""
"If it seems appropriate to the Order, the Order should charge him with "
"deception."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.20"
msgid "Esā ñatti."
msgstr "This is the motion.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.21"
msgid "Suṇātu me, bhante, saṃgho."
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1338</a>Venerables, let the Order listen to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.22"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu pātimokkhe uddissamāne na sādhukaṃ aṭṭhiṃ katvā "
"manasi karoti."
msgstr ""
"This monk so-and-so didn’t pay proper attention when the monastic code was "
"being recited."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.23"
msgid "Saṃgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno mohaṃ āropeti."
msgstr "The Order charges him with deception."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.24"
msgid ""
"Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno mohassa āropanā, so tuṇhassa;"
msgstr ""
"Any monk who approves of charging him with deception should remain silent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.25"
msgid "yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya."
msgstr "Any monk who does not approve should speak up.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.26"
msgid "Āropito saṃghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno moho."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1339</a>The monk so-and-so has been charged with "
"deception by the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.27"
msgid "Khamati saṃghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"The Order approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it "
"thus.’”</p></span>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.28"
msgid "Anāropite mohe moheti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1340</a>If he deceives, but he is not charged with "
"deception, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.1.29"
msgid "Āropite mohe moheti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he deceives, and he is charged with deception, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.2.1"
msgid "Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī moheti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.73.2.2\""
">Bu-Pc.73.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1341</a>If he deceives, and it is a "
"legitimate procedure, and he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.2.2"
msgid "Dhammakamme vematiko moheti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he deceives, and it is a legitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.2.3"
msgid "Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī moheti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he deceives, and it is a legitimate procedure, but he perceives it as "
"illegitimate, <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.46\">BD.3.46</a> he commits "
"an offense entailing confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.2.4"
msgid "Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1342</a>If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he "
"perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.2.5"
msgid "Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.2.6"
msgid "Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an illegitimate procedure, and he perceives it as illegitimate, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.73.2."
"3\">Bu-Pc.73.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1343</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"na vitthārena sutaṃ hoti, ūnakadvattikkhattuṃ vitthārena sutaṃ hoti, na "
"mohetukāmassa, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he has not heard it in full; if he has heard it less than two or three "
"times in full; if he does not want to deceive; if he is insane; if he is the "
"first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc73:2.3.3"
msgid "Mohanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1344</a>The third rule, the "
"training rule on deception, is finished.</p>"
